							Revd Mr Lindberg in Gothenburg. He observed
							in his sermon, that there were several kinds
							of people, who were hindered from enjoying
							the happiness which the Lord would willingly
							bestow upon them, if they would but come in
							the way &amp; order of his appointment. Among
							one of these sorts of well meaning souls, I
							found myself so completely described as if I
							had opened my whole mind to him. He
							remarked that some people thought that if 
							they could arrive at a certain degree of ex
							cessive grief &amp; anguish, &amp; could shed repenting
							tears night &amp; day, that then the Lord 
						
					</p>
